{
  "id": "fd886d3310984f88add78124a0be8694",
  "title": "UltimateHitMarker",
  "description": "UltimateHitMarker system will make adding hit markers to your game a breeze with automatic advanced features",
  "longDescription": "<p><a href=\"https://vimeo.com/698430899/fa5f5e090d\" rel=\"nofollow\">Overview Video</a></p><p><a href=\"https://discord.gg/zYv9RV4p\" rel=\"nofollow\">Discord</a></p><p>UltimateHitMarker system adds the ability to shape how you want your hit markers to appear in your project without compromising on features. Being able to add to your project quickly should be something that you can expect to be able to do and that is what this system allows. You are able to add many features (below) to your project in a few easy steps.</p>",
  "technicalDetails": "<p>The UltimateHitMarker system features support for:</p><ul><li> Supports 3D widgets for easier VR setup</li><li> Both, Niagara and Cascade for the hit particle effect</li><li>Choosing what method you want to use for detecting actor that can be hit (via tags or bones)</li><li>No mess tag conversion (you can add any tags you like to the actors you want to hit and UHM will convert them for you</li><li>Choosing if your game needs to display just the particle effect, just the hit marker, just the damage output text, or any combination of the 3 mentioned</li><li>Easy 1 click debugging to see what went wrong when setting up the UHM component</li><li>Setting up with any hit type to be able to add hit markers (line trace, projectiles, etc)</li><li>Easily adjustable damage multipliers</li><li>Spawning decals based on surface type</li><li>Automatic attachment of decals to any actor that was hit, yes even skeletal meshes (attached to sockets to prevent sliding)</li></ul><p><br /></p><p> </p><p>Number of Blueprints: 6</p><p>Input: Keyboard/ Mouse</p><p>Network Replicated: No (planned)</p><p>Supported Development Platforms:</p><p>Windows: Yes</p><p>Mac: Yes</p><p><br /></p><p>Documentation:</p><p>Comments inside the component and included blueprint</p><p>Video Tutorials (contact me on Discord or by email)</p><p><a href=\"https://discord.gg/zYv9RV4p\" rel=\"nofollow\">Discord</a></p>",
